  "body": " Complete base second-order word expansion   With as above, evaluation of the actual relator for the base class gives Equivalently, Its ramified polar form is For a general determinant class , one has    Lean   We evaluate the square contribution of , the commutator contribution of and , and then polarize the resulting quadratic expression.  Normalize a cohomology representative so that only varies, by . In terms of , the complete base contribution ledger is The starred entries contain ordinary -terms and the -terms of the lifted -action. They occur only as central coordinates of and , and central coordinates do not affect the commutator. Since the lower values of and at the tame map are both the identity, the commutator contribution is exactly the polar form of their -coordinates, .  The first line is the extraspecial case of , but we recall why it remains valid with the -terms present. The class-two identity uses only that the lift of the relevant tame operator is an automorphism of the central extension and fixes the centre; it does not assume that the chosen section is equivariant. If , then and have the same image in , so the identity gives the square of , namely . If , then and the lift of is a central automorphism of order at most , so acts trivially on the class-two coefficient group and the same identity applies.  The factors and have zero -coordinate on the normalized representative, and hence no quadratic central contribution. Multiplying the table gives . Polarizing and using the -invariance of gives ; the operator is invertible by the same polynomial argument used in . Finally, is exactly on the candidate source.   "
