  "number": "6.8",
  "title": "Ramified Hermitian model and Frobenius fixed space.",
  "body": " Ramified Hermitian model and Frobenius fixed space   Let be tame inertia, let be a simple ramified self-dual -module, and write Let be an -invariant nonsingular quadratic form with polar form . Then For one also has Consequently the ramified candidate base form of has .   Lean (Arf vanishing)  Lean (Arf = s)  Lean (main)  Lean   We identify the invariant quadratic form with a Hermitian form, compute its Arf invariant one Hermitian line at a time, and then determine the fixed space of the -primary Frobenius operator.  Put Choose an inertia character over ; then is the additive group of and acts by multiplication by . Since has only the irreducible isomorphism type and , the inverse character lies in the Frobenius orbit of . The character is nontrivial of odd order, so this orbit has even length and Set After an -module identification , the nondegenerate -invariant form is uniquely expressible as Indeed, invariance under multiplication by , nondegeneracy of the trace pairing, and symmetry identify the adjoint involution with and force the matrix to be Hermitian.  Define The scalar lies in , and Thus is linear. It is -invariant, while because the inertia action is nontrivial and is simple. Hence .  Hermitian diagonalization over the finite field extension gives Therefore is an orthogonal sum of the Hermitian-line forms Write . The norm is surjective with fibres of size , and the trace-zero subspace of contains nonzero elements. Hence Each Hermitian line has Arf invariant . Additivity of the Arf invariant proves .  It remains to compute the fixed space of . Over , the inertia weights form one Frobenius cycle, each weight space having multiplicity . Let be the residue modulo of an integer representing . By the defining congruences of , Thus translation by on has cycles, each of length . On one cycle write the successive maps as The product is the action of on . The shift by is trivial modulo , so centralizes inertia; it also commutes with , being a power of . Hence it is a central -element of the faithful tame image. A cyclic -group acting in characteristic has nonzero fixed vectors, and centrality makes its fixed space an -submodule. Simplicity therefore forces on . Consequently a -fixed vector on a cycle is uniquely determined by its component in , and that cycle contributes dimension . There are cycles, proving .  Finally, gives    "
